Date: 3 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health 3 Apr 2003
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

Situation report on atypical pneumonia 3 Apr 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
------------------------
As at 1 PM 3 Apr 2003, an additional 26 patients with symptoms of atypical
pneumonia were admitted to public hospitals. They include 2 healthcare
workers and 2 patients from Amoy Gardens. The remaining 22 were new
patients and contacts of patients with atypical pneumonia.
A total of 98 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have been
discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 9 are discharged today,
including 2 medical students.
Most of the patients currently in hospital are showing positive responses
to the new treatment protocol. 85 of them are receiving treatment in
intensive care unit.
A 56-year-old man with a history of chronic heart disease died in Princess
Margaret Hospital today, bringing to 17 the total number of deaths relating
to atypical pneumonia.
The cumulative figure for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows: (number
of cases with pneumonia are presented in parentheses).
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students 177 (177)
53 of the patients were discharged
Patients, family members & visitors 557 (557)
45 of the patients were discharged
Total admission 734 (734)
98 were discharged
[If any of our subscribers have official information on this new treatment
protocol we would very much appreciate receiving it. Our thanks to Thomas P.
Giordano, MD <tpg@bcm.tmc.edu> for asking for these specifics. - Mod.MPP]
